# Example: Σ feat: Allow users to go through an alternative flow 
# |<----  Using a Maximum Of 100 Characters  ---->|

# Explain why this change is being made
# |<----   Try To Limit Each Line to a Maximum Of 72 Characters   ---->|

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be   (greek type font)
#    Σ feat     (new feature)
#    ω fix      (bug fix)
#    Ξ docs     (changes to documentation)
#    ζ style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    ϋ refactor (refactoring production code)
#    Δ perf     (improving performance)
#    Γ build    (changes to build system, webpack, brocolli, etc)
#    ϑ ci       (changes to ci config files, Jenkinsfile, Travis)
#    π test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    θ chore    (updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change)
#    Ψ revert   (reverts previous commit)
